{"updated_at": "2012-03-24T04:59:11Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-03-24T04:59:11Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4671662", "id": 4671662, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3777", "issue_id": 3777, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/krainboltgreene", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "15d21696a56b183503cf2c82114be9d6", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/15d21696a56b183503cf2c82114be9d6?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F621565b35926d1e7fcfa1f5a8b3740e6.png", "id": 334809, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/events{/privacy}", "login": "krainboltgreene", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krainboltgreene/followers"}, "body": "Because docs are generated static files, and since they should be generate'able at any time, to get the exact same state across any environment it should remain out of git.\r\n\r\nIf 5 developers can download a repository, run some generator, and get the same output, then that output shouldn't be added to the repository since it can't be \"lost\" and doesn't need versioning. If you version both the documentation and the code with the documentation you're versioning 1 thing twice, with the second wrapped in a ton of HTML and CSS.", "_id": {"$oid": "523831c8bd3543c15100f7f0"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3777#issuecomment-4671662"}
